==History==
[[File:Vox (2014 european elections in Spain).svg|thumb|300px|right|Results of Vox (2014 European elections in Spain)]]
Vox was founded on 17 December 2013,<ref>[https://www.voxespana.es/index.php/aviso-legal "VOX es un partido político con personalidad jurídica propia e inscrito en el Registro de partidos políticos del Ministerio del Interior el día 17 Diciembre de 2013"] - ''VOX''</ref> and publicly launched at a press conference in [[Madrid]] on 16 January 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.libertaddigital.com/espana/politica/2014-01-14/nace-el-partido-politico-de-abascal-y-ortega-lara-1276508230/|title=Nace Vox, el partido político de Santiago Abascal y Ortega Lara|publisher=Libertad Digital|date=14 January 2014|accessdate=16 March 2014}}</ref><ref name="Reuters1">{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/01/16/us-spain-politics-idUSBREA0F1HM20140116|title=Spanish ruling party rebels launch new conservative party|last=O'Leary|first=Elisabeth|date=|work=U.S.|accessdate=2018-04-18|archiveurl=|archivedate=|deadurl=|language=en-US}}</ref> The reasons for this schism seem to be the way the incumbent PP government dealt with the issue of the violence of separatist group [[ETA (separatist group)|ETA]], the fiscal policy of the PP and the desire for a more [[centralized government]] in contrast to the current, quasi-federal political system ("[[Autonomous communities of Spain|State of Autonomies]]") instituted in 1978. Vox opposes [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|Basque]] and [[Catalonia|Catalan]] separatism in general.<ref name="Reuters1" /> VOX have labelled themselves as a right-wing and [[Christian democracy|Christian democratic]] party. The first provisional chairman was the philosopher [[:es:José_Luis_González_Quirós|José Luis González Quirós]] (provisional until the party's internal election in late 2014). Other members are [[Santiago Abascal]] and [[José Antonio Ortega Lara]] (well known for having been kidnapped by ETA for more than a year).

Vox ran for the first time in the [[European Parliament election, 2014 (Spain)|2014 European elections]] but narrowly failed to win a seat in the [[European Parliament]].<ref>[http://www.libertaddigital.com/espana/2014-05-26/tristeza-y-decepcion-en-vox-tras-los-resultados-de-las-elecciones-europeas-1276519600/ Tristeza y decepción en Vox tras los resultados de las Elecciones Europeas] in libertaddigital.com {{es}}</ref>

In September 2014 the party elected Santiago Abascal, one of the founders, as new President, and Iván Espinosa de los Monteros, also a founder, as General Secretary. Eleven members of the National Executive Committee were also elected.

As of 2017 Vox remains a marginal political actor in Spain.<ref name=":0">{{cite news|url=https://www.eldiario.es/politica/Vox-derecha-extrema-prospera-juzgados_0_718828397.html|title=Vox: la ultraderecha irrelevante en las urnas agita los juzgados|work=eldiario.es|accessdate=2018-04-18|language=es}}<br/>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/03/27/world/europe/spain-catalonia-carles-puigdemont-extradition.html|title=Arrest of Catalan Leader Tests Spain, Separatists and E.U.|date=2018-03-27|work=The New York Times|accessdate=2018-04-18|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> In the fall of 2017 the number of members increased 20% in forty days as a consequence of the terrorist attack in Barcelona and the Catalan independence process.<ref name=":1">{{cite news|url=http://www.publico.es/politica/afiliacion-partido-ultraderechista-vox-aumenta-20-40-dias.html|title=La afiliación al partido ultraderechista VOX aumenta un 20% en 40 días|accessdate=2018-04-18|language=es-ES}}</ref>

After the [[Catalan independence referendum, 2017|Catalan referendum]] of 2017 and the start of a [[Spanish constitutional crisis]], Vox opted to not participate in the [[Catalan regional election, 2017|Catalan regional elections of 2017]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.elplural.com/politica/2017/11/03/vox-el-21d-es-fruto-de-un-pacto-oculto-entre-rajoy-y-los-golpistas|title=VOX: "El 21D es fruto de un pacto oculto entre Rajoy y los golpistas"|last=Paradinas|first=Marcos|date=3 November 2017|work=[[elplural.com]]|access-date=18 April 2018|language=es}}</ref> After the [[Catalan declaration of independence]], the party sued the [[Parliament of Catalonia]] and several independentist politicians.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://elpais.com/ccaa/2017/10/11/catalunya/1507707978_302026.html|publisher=El País|date=11 October 2017|accessdate=30 August 2018|language=es|title=El TSJ catalán admite la querella de Vox por rebelión contra Puigdemont}}</ref>

On 10 September 2018 Vox enlisted an independent legislator in the regional parliament of Extremadura (who had dropped out of the PP parliamentary group) as party member.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regiondigital.com/noticias/extremadura/298894-los-ex-populares-juan-antonio-morales-y-antonio-pozo-se-incorporan-a-vox.html|publisher=Región Digital|language=es-ES|date=10 September 2018|accessdate=19 November 2018|title=Los ex 'populares' Juan Antonio Morales y Antonio Pozo se incorporan a Vox}}</ref> On 2 December 2018 they won 12 parliamentary seats in the [[2018 Andalusian regional election|Andalusian regional election]].<ref>[https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-46422036 Spain far-right Vox party gains foothold in Andalusia election] Published by BBC news on 3 December 2018</ref>

== Ideology ==
Vox takes a [[pro-life]] stance on abortion and opposes same-sex marriage because they consider the Spanish word for marriage, "matrimonio", to be etymologically inadequate for same sex couples. Vox seeks to create a new type of union, called a "civil union", to replace same-sex marriage.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?feature=youtu.be&v=qCro2WYc4Zc|title=Alejo Vidal Cuadras, fundador de VOX habla sobre el matrimonio homosexual.|last=|first=|date=|website=www.google.com|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-09-03}}</ref>

Starting with a focus in economically liberal stances and [[centralism|recentralization]] proposals, the focus of their message shifted towards stances compatible with European [[right-wing populism]],<ref name="casals">{{cite journal|last=Casals|first=Xavier|author-link=Xavier Casals|date=21 April 2015|title=Vox y su campaña contra la inmigración masiva|url=http://www.elmanifiesto.com/articulos.asp?idarticulo=5047|journal=ElManifiesto.com}}</ref> endorsing anti-Islam and anti mass-immigration discourses as well as [[criticism of multiculturalism]].<ref name="casals" /> Their view of [[European Union]] is that of a [[Euroscepticism|soft euroscepticism]], arguing that Spain should make no [[sovereignty]] concessions to the EU, because they consider Spanish sovereignty to reside in the Spanish [[nation]] alone.<ref name=":2">{{Cite news|url=https://www.libertaddigital.com/opinion/santiago-abascal/cadiz-covadonga-y-bruselas-77185/|title=Cádiz, Covadonga y Bruselas|last=Abascal|first=Santiago|date=2015-11-08|work=Libertad Digital|accessdate=2018-07-21|language=es-ES|quote=Porque estamos convencidos de que nación y soberanía son conceptos íntimamente relacionados. Si somos soberanos es porque somos una Nación y no tenemos derecho a entregar lo que hemos recibido de nuestros mayores. España debe estar en Europa pero sin complejos, reivindicando el papel histórico, industrial y agrícola que merecemos. No debemos ser vasallos de Merkel ni de Tsipras. Ni camareros de Merkel ni paganos de las propinas de Tsipras. Las Cortes de Cádiz proclamaron que la Nación española era libre e independiente y que no podía ser patrimonio de ninguna familia o persona. Proclamaron asimismo que la soberanía reside esencialmente en la Nación, que es la única que tiene derecho a establecer sus leyes fundamentales. Esta declaración de soberanía ha sido una constante en toda nuestra historia constitucional.}}</ref> However, they propose to remove Spain's [[Autonomous communities of Spain|autonomous communities]], negating the sovereignty of other [[Nationalities and regions of Spain|nationalities]] and [[National and regional identity in Spain|regional identities]] within Spain.<ref name=":2" />

